Description: Rim fragment of a pottery plate or bowl; cream wash, black stripe on inside of mouth and on edge of rim. Hard, yellow-orange clay, Munsell 7.5YR 8/6 (reddish yellow).
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 328)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
